cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.SE, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of IoT and cloud technologies for efficient resource management in Smart Cities. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper explores the social implications of the sensing as a service model. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the economic aspects of the sensing as a service model. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of software applications as services in Smart Cities. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still relevant as the paper discusses the use of cloud technologies for offering infrastructure and platforms as services.
